# Implementation Plan: Long-term Stability & Memory Safety

## Problem Description
Long-running sessions (e.g., several hours) occasionally trigger a `std::queue::front()` assertion failure in the GStreamer `libcamerasrc` plugin (`std::unique_ptr<RequestWrap>`). 
This is likely caused by system stress due to:
1.  **Memory Exhaustion**: The [EventRecorder](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/buffer/EventRecorder.cpp#6-14) has an unbounded `pending_events_` queue. Frequent AI detections (noisy environment) can cause memory usage to grow without limit, especially if network transmission is slow.
2.  **Resource Contention**: High AI load coupled with memory pressure leads to driver-level timeouts and internal GStreamer state corruption.

## Proposed Changes

### Event Recording Management (Memory Safety)

#### [MODIFY] [EventRecorder.h](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/buffer/EventRecorder.h)
- Add `MAX_PENDING_EVENTS` constant (e.g., 5).
- Add a mechanism to check queue size before pushing.

#### [MODIFY] [EventRecorder.cpp](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/buffer/EventRecorder.cpp)
- Update [triggerEvent()](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/buffer/EventRecorder.cpp#21-37) to drop the event if `pending_events_.size() >= MAX_PENDING_EVENTS`.
- Add logging for dropped events.

---

### AI Detection Cooldown (Stability)

#### [MODIFY] [AppConfig.h](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/config/AppConfig.h)
- Add `EVENT_COOLDOWN_SEC` (e.g., 5 seconds).

#### [MODIFY] [StreamPipeline.cpp](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/stream/StreamPipeline.cpp)
- Implement a per-track cooldown timer. Even if the AI still detects "falling", don't trigger a new recording until the cooldown expires.

---

### Monitoring & Diagnostics

#### [MODIFY] [SystemResourceMonitor.h](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/system/SystemResourceMonitor.h)
- Add `pending_event_count` to [DeviceStatus](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/system/IResourceMonitor.h#10-24) struct.

#### [MODIFY] [SubCamController.cpp](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/controller/SubCamController.cpp)
- Pass the [EventRecorder](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/buffer/EventRecorder.cpp#6-14)'s current queue size to the monitor or directly into the network facade.

#### [MODIFY] [NetworkFacade.cpp](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/network/NetworkFacade.cpp)
- Include the `pending_events` count in the `AVAILABLE` (0x05) JSON payload.

## Verification Plan

### Automated Tests
- Run the system with a "noisy" AI mock that triggers falls every second.
- Monitor memory usage via [top](file:///c:/Users/1-05/Downloads/SubCameraApp_refactory/src/network/NetworkFacade.cpp#35-42) or the `AVAILABLE` network packets.
- Verify that memory usage stays capped as events are dropped.

### Manual Verification
- Long-run soak test (8+ hours) on a Raspberry Pi 4.
- Verify that the `RequestWrap` assertion does not occur even during high load.
